(secondQuint)Long-term Adverse Effects After Bariatric Surgery on Bone Density.

 Bariatric surgery shows impressive results in terms of weight loss and resolution of comorbidities.

 Still, there are questions as to the frequency of long-term adverse effects: data on alterations in bone health are missing, The goal of this trial is to examine long-term effects of laparoscopic gastric bypass (LRYGB) and sleeve gastrectomy (LSG) on bone mineral density, fracture risk, and body composition 5 years post-surgery.

